mum TSP contribution percentage or an amount that will result in you reaching the elective deferral limit by the end of the year and 3 You are at least 50 years old in the year that the catch up contributions are made even if your birthday is December 31 of that year and 4 You are not in the 6 month non contribution period following the receipt of a financial hardship in service withdrawal ANNUAL CATCH UP LIMITS If you meet the above eligibility criteria you can make catch up contributions not to exceed the annual catch up contribution limit The maximum catch up contribution for 2003 is 2 000 This limit will increase to 3 000 in 2004 4 000 in 2005 and 5 000 in 2006 After 2006 this amount will be subject to increases to reflect inflation ELECTIONS DOC employees must make their elections using http www employeeexpress gov emain htm Employee Express Employee Express will be ready to accept elections no earlier than July 28 2003 Elections submitted in July become effective during the first full pay period in August 2003 After that time you can elect to make catch up contributions at any time during the year as long as you do not exceed the annual catch up limit You can elect to have any whole dollar amount deducted from your basic pay each pay period Your election will terminate when you reach the annual catch up limit or the calendar year ends or you elect to stop the contribution Since your catch up election automatically terminates at the end of each year you need to submit a new election using Employee Express when you want to start catch up contributions for the next year Check for additional information on the http www tsp gov TSP website If you still have questions your contacts at MASC are Yolanda Pacheco 303 497 7383 for clients with last names beginning A thru J and Lori Osborn 303 497 6524 for clients with last names beginning K thru Z Top Go To Top Last update on 07 July 2003 Mail comments to mailto Janice Kolk noaa gov Janice Kolk Mountain Administrative Su